The paper discusses programming language approaches to concurrency and communication-centric software, which falls under the category of programming languages (cs.PL) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). The paper also mentions new program analysis techniques and implementation mechanisms, which are relevant to software engineering (cs.SE) and logic in computer science (cs.LO). Finally, the paper may also touch upon data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) in the context of designing new programming language features and type systems.
